			<abstract>Color slides by Fred M. Springer, from his collection of approximately 50,000 photographs, which he and his wife, Dale, donated to the Center in 2012. The collection spans more than fifty years, six continents, thirty countries, and forty states. Major areas of focus include steam in both regular service and on tourist and scenic railroads, structures including depots and engine terminals, and railroads in the landscape.</abstract>
